caption: I’ve never been here but somehow they got my phone number and illegally spam me with text messages.

I came here for their lunch buffet and I was very amazed by the amount of selections they had out. They had about 8 dishes you can choose and eat from and the best part is you can sit in their backyard patio and eat. All of the dishes were rich in spices and taste. It was a very good experience and I can’t wait to bring couple of heads back to try out more stuff. The service here was also very pleasant and sweet.
I ordered for delivery and the food arrived on time and fresh.
This place is awesome! Fair pricing, large portions and the staff are consistently kind.
Really enjoyed their food - the eggplant dish was outta this world.
Great food and customer service ! Loved the chicken tikka masala, chili chicken and samosa chaat 👌🏽

This place is the best!! If I could bathe in the chicken tikka masala sauce, I would 1000% do it. Also, we got it delivered—so fast btw—and the food was still super hot when it got here! 12/10 experience. Lastly, I never leave reviews of restaurants (I just never think to) but when you find a gem like this you gotta spread the word!
The food is great!!!
The food was great. Good service
Outstanding Indian food with a TON of vegetarian and vegan options

The food here seems tasty, but it was difficult to tell bc it was nearly frozen by the time we got it. We were given an hour window for its arrival and told it was on its way when we called after 75 minutes. When we inquired 2 hours after we ordered, we were told it had been delivered. The delivery guy left it on our stoop in the snow and neither called, rang the doorbell, nor knocked; I was sitting right next to the door. While I understand delivery guys can be late, it is cruel and incompetent to leave food out where it freezes or can get stolen. Their flavor profiles seemed promising, but the experience ordering from here was so traumatic that I'm not sure I could do it again. Order with PLENTY of time to spare, but I'm not sure what to advise in terms of discerning that it's been delivered and sitting for an hour in the snow. I'm starting to wonder if they were messing w us for ordering on Seamless (I saw later on their website that they use another online service). Maybe they'll be nicer if customers use that.

I ordered Rasmalai from Uber eats and it was spoilt, milk in it was curdled. I was really disappointed. Malai Kofta was really delicious. Vegetable Jalfrezi was not tasty. I think they should really take care about the quality of food they send to customers.
It’s pretty good up I like it

Excellent!  If you want Indian food that tastes homemade or made from scratch, this is your place. What they serve is not the same generic Indian you get at other places. I’ve eaten at just about every Indian restaurant in the city and the food here is uniquely its own. I’ve ordered a variety of different dishes here and they’ve all been excellent and tasty. The service and staff are always friendly and welcoming.
Easily the best Indian food ive had in America!

Have only ordered takeout/delivery from here, but the food alone deserves the 5 stars. Great taste! It’s pricey, but I feel it’s well worth it. Wish the Naan came with all the plates given the prices, but you can always order it extra.

two days ago was our first time we visited this good restaurant. But It is surely not the last time. We enjoyed the evening very much with the excellent service, with the high quality  dishes and fine drinks and with the friendly price. We will definitely return there again.
Delicious Ondian dishes
This spot is one of my favorites! Convenient prices, large dishes and the employees are regularly super friendly.
I had an amazing experience at this restaurant. We liked the awesome vibes and the menu. The waiters are super attentive. I am happy we finally decided to eat here.

First visit and definitely not the last. The ambiance was very inviting along with the aromas. Our server was very informative and knew what to recommend after we spoke about our food likes. We had chick peas with onion and tomato sauce and Naan bread for starters. Our main dishes were Indian spiced Prawns on a bed of sauteed broccoli and potatoes.  Claybowl of Lamb and Spiced rice with a side order of Indian bread stuffed with chopped Lamb meat. DELICIOUS.

The best Indian food. We go every Sunday and sit in their lovey backyard. If it's raining, we do delivery. Staff is so nice and food is top notch. Get the salmon tikka (fresh, generous portion, healthy); the saag mushroom; eggplant bharta, and chicken curry hara maas. All Amazing!

I told my friends about this restaurant with my highest recommendations. I go their often. This recommendation is always successful. The the cooking is flavorable and the stuff is very friendly and cooperative. Every time  we visit this place we have a gorgeous time.  I warmly recommend this restaurant.

This place is amazing. I didn’t know what I wanted for dinner and then there it is right in front of me. I ordered Saag Paneer, Garlic Naan and Tandoori Malai Kabob (chicken). This is by far the best Indian I’ve had in 7+ years!!! Maybe forever! Everything was perfect. Cooked just right, fresh, flavorful and done early for pick up. I’ll ABSOLUTELY return here soon for more!!!
The samosa masala was perfect, good and friendly service.
Seriously good curries and breads at laughably reasonable prices. For some of the best Indian food in Brooklyn, look no further.
I simply liked their food. I always get excellent customer service there. The place is well organised and the employees are always super friendly. Keep up the good work.
I regularly come buying some food in this place. I love the prompt service and well prepared food. Fantastic work.

I sent my friends to this place with my highest recommendations. I  go to this restaurant often. I get very good feedback from my friends. The dishes they serve are tasty and the team is attentive and cooperative. Every time  we visit this place we pass a pleasing time.  I recommend this place with pleasure.
The place is first-rate and broad, the food was enchanting and the prices were very affordable. fast, productive service and very personal staff. Recommended.
If this place ever closes I will cry. Best Indian food in the neighborhood - I rely on this place. Excellent naan and perfect tikka masala. Go here!!
Great food, great service. Not overcrowded.
Lunch buffet is delicious and a great value.
No frills Indian restaurant. Friendly staff. A bit grungy. Tasty buffet, very reasonable for Park Slope.

You have to order nann, milk tea separately even though it is  lunch buffet. Also no rice pudding for lunch buffet.. The waiter even didn't mention anything when I ordered it. the food was good but I would't go back for lunch buffet there.
Had masala chai and gulab jamun. It was served warm. So delicious.  Clean. Friendly service.
Everything is fresh and delish!!

So the reason i am giving it 1 star is because i ordered a paratha which did not look or taste like a paratha from any angle i ordered chai and it didnt taste like chai it tasted like water with chai color. ☹ i was so disappointed
Very friendly staff. Food is ok. Nothing that stood out. The goat curry was tasty but we ended up with more bones than meat. The cheese naan was bland. Overall, forgettable.
This place stands alone. Good price, good food and far enough away from home to keep me from coming back to often.
So Yummy, the service was amazing, and the meal(s) were delicious!
Good service and good quality food. Taste on curries could be stronger for an Indian palette. Ordered saag paneer and vegetable tikka masala (pass on this).
Food was hot, a little bland but the Naans were excellent - would highly recommend the Pishwari naan. Wait times not too bad and service was fine.
We have not been this satisfied with Indian food since living in the UK. This food is VERY good.
Excellent food and service. Very friendly and kind staff.
I just loved their dishes. I always get excellent service there. The place is always clean and the cashiers are always very friendly. Will come back again.
I’ve had way better food ! The employees had a snotty attitude and I guess it’s because the slow business they receive here

Used to be great but now consistently unpredictable.  Sometimes it’s great, sometimes it’s just plain bad.  We always order the same dish - malai kofta. Last order a couple of weeks ago was fantastic, perfectly cooked and balanced in terms of creaminess, salt and spice.  The order before that was awful with the kofta entirely undercooked and the flavors way off.  Tonight, for the first time ever the malai kofta sauce was full of chopped onion which was overwhelming.  Pretty frustrating to say the least so we will make a switch to a better restaurant when we find it, which is difficult, as good Indian is hard to come by in this part of Brooklyn.
This spot is worth a visit. They serve big portions for fair rates. Always clean and with great mood. I highly recommend this place.

Got delivery from here, some real good shahi paneer and saag paneer. Unfortunately the naans are made with egg and the samosas are fried with the meat, but that seems par for the course for America :(
Had a fantastic experience in this spot with my son. The food was served quickly and the service is just awesome. Prices are reasonable.
I very much like the food and customer service, fantastic area next to my house. The cashiers are always friendly. Would recommend to others.
Food was fantastic and the service was super nice.!

Wonderful spices, elegant balance, fresh ginger and peppers, not relying on sugary sweet dishes like many Indian restaurants. The chutneys are bright and taste like coriander and tamarind, not mint and ketchup. These are the kind of people who care about the food they make.
Stale food. Horrible experience with the buffet.
Save ur self
Good service, great food and great decor. They have good seating for slightly large groups and nice tables for dates. If come here again for sure.
Great food, great service. Thank you!

When you first walk in the Ambiance and the Aromas are very enticing. The waiter service is prompt and very knowledgeable and their recommendations were delicious based on the type of food we liked. Recommended very highly.
I really like their dishes. I always get fantastic service there. The place is neat and the employees are always welcoming. I highly recommend this place.
The food is regularly well prepared and delicious, staff members provides great customer service. I really like how clean it is and mood. Keep up the good work.
Great garlic naan and the buffet had a strong concise selection of good food :)
Delicious and affordable lunch buffet. Really nice people work here, great vibes. Will definitely be back regularly.

Thats the naan I ordered from them few hours ago and the rest of the food was so oily and didn’t have any taste, my mother got diarrhea cause the food wasn’t cooked and prepared well. PLEASE DONT WASTE YOUR MONEY ON THIS RESTAURANT!!!
Go for the buffet, cant go wrong with a nice Indian food buffet.
Really yummy!!
Food was not great and is expensive
Okay this is one of the best alien food restaurants that we ever been to amazing flavors good prices owner and staff were on top of everything recommended 150% great service and food.

My first experience having Indian food. The food was out of this world! It actually make me want to move to India!!!!! We had chicken kebab, the chicken masala ( best sauce I've ever had in my life!) And chicken curry with coconut sauce. Coconut rice a must-have! You should also try the tomato coconut soup! everything was so delicious that I'm sad that we don't leave by here, we're from South Florida. Must try!!!!!!!!
OMG the food was so amazing I never thought I liked Indian food but this changed my mind completely seasoning is so amazimg once your done eating you feel so great and u want to roll out of here☺️

Really nice place to eat. The food is excellent and the prices are fantastic for the amount of food you get. This is definitely one of those restaurants that is inexpensive enough to make it a go-to if you're in the mood for Indian cuisine.
Lovely food. Specially biriyani.
Good, nothing special

{Vegetarians Avoid } We were tourists n were near dumbo, wanted to try something near Brooklyn. Took a subway of 30mins to reach this place with good reviews on net. We were disappointed to see very less veg options in buffet (no Paneer dish was there, no appetizers, only one sweet item like rava chikdi which tasted bland , 2 varieties of aloo n one mix veg, 1 dal for vegetarians .. Is this called buffet? Off course non vegetarians had some options) n then we 2 sat for buffet n got 1 whole naan cut to 4 slices..they told they will serve naan to table in buffet...we ordered for 1 more as it not sufficient. To our surprise they charged for that extra naan in “All you can eat Buffet” , that too he never told it would cost extra while ordering...This is not correct if you have advertised as all you can eat buffet...Place was small, I understand it’s New York but the service we weren’t happy as vegetarians..
Excellent buffet great food attentive service.

Me and my boyfriend ordered so much food and literally we ate every little last crumb. The food was amazing. We ordered a fish dish, a spicy chicken dish, the cheese naan, and the mint lemonade. For some reason the food on the table had an illusion of looking like smaller portions but we both came in super hungry and left super full. Try the cheese naan! I was skeptical at first but it isn't overly cheesy so you can eat it with any dish you get.
Traditional Indian restaurant with  a quaint outdoor space and excellent authentic cuisine. The  friendly waiters offer great service.  The lamb curry will melt in your mouth.
Fantastic service and food, at a great price . We've been there several times at this point and will definitely return. Our favorite Indian restaurant in Brooklyn!
One of the few places where in dining and delivery are both 5-star. The back patio is gorgeous, amazing lunch buffet, and great quality all around.
Awesome! awesome! awesome! I’ve been coming here for a while now and almost everyday since they started the all you can eat lunch buffet. I would give 10 stars if I could.

This place is one of our favorite Indian spots in Park slope. The food is so delicious and their garlic naan is the best I ever had. It's very cute and cozy inside. The lemon rice paired really nicely with the sauces. We had excellent service here and will definitely be coming back for more.
Nice place, cozy and warm. Good food. My favorite is chicken vindaloo.
I found it being a little bit expensive compared to other Indian places around that area. But food and service was great.
Great spot,  CLEAN,  AWESOME BUFFET,  LOW PRICE OF ONLY $12  THIS IS A MUST TO DINE at! Simply delectable and affordable
My wife and I enjoyed the food and service very much
Really delicious and authentic food.
Very good buffet and reasonable  price and family environment  and very good location

These 5 stars are only for the clean facility, good Service, mutton curry and masala chicken. Strongly urge the management to change or expand the menu. Also, please change that ugly big old rice pot, it looks nasty, and finally, would appreciate if you can have more than one style of rice too, like fried rice or potato rice or something new. Pleae make this good place a great one. But dont change the price.
Naan was very good although a little more burnt than I’d like. The food was OK, not bad but not great. I rounded up from 3.5 stars because of the naan and nice employees.
Excellent food, reasonable prices, and friendly service. Definitely my new go to for Indian cuisine.
One of the best Indian places I've eaten at so far.
50% chance you'll get the juiciest chicken you've ever had, or you get a dry rock in your mouth. Great food regardless
Satisfying food, well made and with very friendly service = yum!

The place is a bit small but it's still very pleasant. Great staff and food. They also have a nice $12 all you can eat lunch buffet which is great value compared to regular menu prices. The tea is amazing lol

This is first time here. We really enjoyed the food. It's delicious. Staff are friendly and professional. We are going back soon. My friends like to come here . No question about it. You must try. Believe it or not!
Yummy food and great service
My new favorite Indian buffet in NY! Everything was flavorful and delicious. And very nice service.
Had the lunch buffet here. Average selections and average to above average quality. Service was ok. It was hot outside when I was there and too hot inside in my opinion. Just average.

Went here this Sunday with my best friend.  We are really into spicy food so we asked them to turn it up.  DELICIOUS!  Sometimes you get that spiciness that isn't quite fresh so it just burns but doesn't have the flavors,  or you get a place that doesn't want to turn it up, but Namaste provided!  The food was fresh and complex and wonderful, and the service was gracious.  Go here if you love great spice, but if you're squeamish you should go anyway because they are very accommodating.  Get the buffet or order from the menu you won't be disappointed!
Sensational food; sensational price; highly recommended!
Delicious food and extremely courteous service! Highly recommended, plus their 10$ lunch buffet is slammin!!
Wonderful staff, food is delicious and reasonably priced.

These guys are soooo nice.  I ordered delivery, and they had forgotten my tea... I called them a week later, because I had forgotten about it...  they delivered it!  And because I'm absent minded, I realized that they hadn't actually charged me the first time I had ordered it.  They new that too but delivered it anyway.  What nice people.  Oh, the food is always great there.  I go all the time.
$12 lunch buffet was really good!
Wonderful samosas and appetizers! Top rate service with a personal touch. Great find!
Nice food
Great food, great prices
I have came here multiple times and had nothing but satisfaction. The service is outstanding and the food is marvelous! Authentic Indian Food!
Nothing Short of awesome
The food and service were great

I have never had such great Indian food. The service was absolutely phenomenal. The staff treated you as if they knew you a lifetime. It's a nice cozy environment.. just perfect for an intimate date. You will NOT be disappointed!
Good food always.  Nice spread. Helpful service.  Clean . Meters parking best not to drive.
Food is good, but delivery mistakes can be avoided in future for long wait time and wrong item getting delivered.

The buffet is really affordable compared to others 12$ without tax you can eat what you want. Although as good as it sounds, they don't really have that many options. Today I was feeling like Indian food and instead of going to a takeout I wanted to try out different things. I have tried some of the Indian dishes before, even though I don't remember exact names, taste was familiar and I could recognize some of them. The food was quite bland/overcooked it seemed that it was sitting there since the opening. When I came in there was a couple and usually that's an indicator that something might be wrong with the place. The server really tried to be as nice as possible, he kept coming to check if I need some water and brought some bread (which was only thing that I really liked since it was fresh). There was another guy, my guess he was a chief, he had some radio on his phone that was really loud and he was walking around, then he started to talk really loudly with someone at the back and it just felt like I don't even exist for him. I left feeling full but not satisfied with the food, it just filled me up, that's all.
Excellent service and good food
Amazing Food!!
Good Indian food in Park Slope. I’m a big fan of the samosa here — very crunchy and well made.
The buffet is good for the price $13 with tax. The items are not great but not bad too. Overall the lunch buffet is good.
Great Indian food
Real delicious Indian food with a cozy backyard. Loved it!
Food is very delicious 🤗🤗🤗

I have been to their lunch buffet twice. Although the food was average, a couple of points that discourage me from visiting them again:  1) I seriously question their ethics. After we were done with the food, I was served the bill without an itemized breakdown. I felt it was too high for what we had ordered. My request to show the itemized bill was received coldly. What I found out though was they had overcharged me by about 50% by adding items I never ordered. Anyone visiting them should carefully look into the bill before paying.  2) During my second visit, they were stingy serving the bread, which is not served in the buffet area but brought to the table upon request.

Have been here for Lunch today, Across the street there was a carnival (Street Fair) and we preferred an option for Buffet. Most miserable food ever. 2 stars are for Chana Masala and Water. And as an Indian I would rather say Nameste (No Thank You) to Nameste.
great food
Decent Indian food, solid but nothing fancy.  They do have this cauliflower tempura in a spicy ketchup sauce that is different.  Service is attentive.

The owners and staff offer great service. You feel like you are visiting friends instead of going to a restaurant. Every dish I've gotten had been wonderful. I only wish I could learn not to over order. I love the fact that they always want to make sure I have enough wine with my meal. Someday I hope I can make it in for lunch on a weekday. I've been doing to try the buffet.
Cheap buffet brunch with tasty food! It is a peaceful atmosphere with really nice people. All you can eat buffet. I recommend the samosas and the dal/cauliflower.
Great American-Indian fusion. Very fresh. Expensive.

Food was horrible. Chicken hard like a rock. I thought chicken marinated yougurt was tender instead it was dry and no taste. Vegetables curry was mostly sauce very little vegetables. Gave us tge impression that the food was left overs from e days ago. Never will go back again.
Nice place, great atmosphere. Came for the lunch buffet starving, and enjoyed the food, especially the balance of spices.

I am in love with this restaraunt. Not only was my Paneer utterly delicious, the waiter was kind of enough to make me a special Ayurvedic tea that was not even on the menu-- of tumeric, ginger and black pepper. So generous, so kind-- fabulous food. Highly recommend.

The best! We knew nothing about this restaurant and luckily tripped into it! Best naan ever and everything else that we ordered was fabulous, fresh and beautifully presented!  Service was extraordinary! Will definitely be going back on our next trip to NYC!

Unfortunately, I don't live in Brooklyn. Otherwise, I would come here all the time. I was here on business and ate here by myself a few times. The owner is extremely nice and the service is excellent. The food is very high quality and substantial. I will definitely be back whenever I'm in Brooklyn.

I came here for the weekend buffet.  It's a pretty good deal for $12 from 11am-4pm on Saturdays and Sundays.  The food itself was okay.  The goat was pretty tough, not very tender.  The sauces were all very watery and not very flavorful.  The naan was tasty though.  The service was good though, very attentive and fast.  It's a decent place to get Indian food if you're ever in the Park Slope neighborhood.
awesome food, must try grilled mushrooms, chicken tikka masala and onion kulcha! great staff and superb service!

Amazing Indian food. Served in good quantity, tastes amazing & authentic. Really enjoyed garlic butter naan & eggplant masala. Courteous staff, good ambience. Overall, a perfect restaurant for authentic Indian food....would definitely visit again.
